\nabla^{2}p=\frac{\partial^{2}\rho}{\partial t^{2}}+\nabla\cdot\nabla\cdot\rho\mathbf{u}\mathbf{u}+\nabla\cdot\nabla\cdot\boldsymbol{\tau}_{ij}-\nabla\cdot\rho\mathbf{g}.\label{eq:wasatch-pressure-poisson-eq}
